Vunani Limited said on Wednesday its headline earnings a share rose to 25.2 cents in the year ended February compared with 19.2 cents last year.
Vunani’s revenue jumped to 350.9 million from R184.2 million last year, while its profit edged up to R45.6 million from R40 million.
Vunani is an independent black-owned and managed diversified financial services group operating three business units in asset management, investment banking and property.
– African News Agency (ANA)




